    <div class="wrapper no-bpadding">
        <h2 class="mf-header mf-section-header">Districts and States</h2>
        <p class="mf-copy">The film is effective at the school level, but even more powerful on the district or state level. Bringing the film to all school communities will align interests and generate enthusiasm for moving learning experiences forward.  We’re already seeing impressive results when a district superintendent takes the lead in</p>
    </div>
    <div class="big-wrapper no-bpadding">
      <div class="horizontal-list-container">
        <ul class="horizontal-list">
          <li class="horizontal-list-item">
            <span class="letter list-order-indicator">A</span>
            <p class="list-copy">getting school board members, senior staff, and school principals to see the film</p>
          </li>
          <li class="horizontal-list-item">
            <span class="letter list-order-indicator">B</span>
            <p class="list-copy">highlighting innovative initiatives already underway</p>
          </li>
          <li class="horizontal-list-item">
            <span class="letter list-order-indicator">C</span>
            <p class="list-copy">formulating the design principles that will shape go-forward strategy</p>
          </li>
          <li class="horizontal-list-item">
            <span class="letter list-order-indicator">D</span>
            <p class="list-copy">show the film to school communities across the district (or state) as a means of generating excitement and commitment for strategic initiatives.</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="button-container">
        <a class="articles-button" href="http://52.74.90.55/" target="_blank">Pam Moran Interview</a>
        <a class="articles-button" href="http://52.74.90.55/" target="_blank">Max McGee Interview</a>
      </div>
      <p class="mf-copy">And consider this <a href="http://us5.campaign-archive2.com/?u=1e1dd398adb9d9bf6231fdfab&id=6351a07db0&e=fa8c57485c" class="black-copy-link" target="_blank">e-mail</a> update from Dr. Michael Mathews, Superintendent of School for the Manhattan Beach Unified School District. Note they drew an audience of 900 to see <i>Most Likely To Succeed</i>, and generated energy and commitment for innovation in their district.</p>
